text: 33 (thirty-three) is a natural or counting number. It comes between thirty-two and thirty-four, and is an odd number. It is divisible by 1, 3, 11, and 33. == In movies == The 33 is a Spanish movie about workers struggle to survive after a disaster strikes in copper and gold mine. == In religion == In the Bible, Noah's name was mentioned 33 times when God made a promise or covenant with him. In superstitions, 33 is believed to be an angel number which means growth and development. == References == Category:Integers
